      • onConnected

        public void onConnected(long total,
               boolean isRangeSupport)
        Description copied from interface: CallBack

        if ConnectTaskImpl is successfully connected with the http/https server this method will be invoke. If not method CallBack.onFailed(DownloadException) will be invoke.

        Specified by:
        onConnected in interface CallBack
        Parameters:
        total - The length of the file. See URLConnection.getContentLength()
        isRangeSupport - indicate whether download can be resumed from pause. See ConnectTaskImpl.run(). If the value of http header field Accept-Ranges is bytes the value of isRangeSupport is true else false
